{
    "name": "Chimera",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Chimera",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary pg. 63",
                        "alt": "Bestiary pg. 63",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                    },
                    "page": 63
                }
            ],
            "html": "The chimera is the archetypal example of an unnatural monster made up of a monstrous mix of wildly different component creatures: in this case, a lion, a dragon, and a goat. Wild, hateful, and hungry, it tries to eat any creature it sees, but sometimes a strong-willed master is able to compel a chimera to serve as a guardian or even a mount.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"563\" game-obj=\"Rules\">Recall Knowledge - Beast</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"2\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Arcana</a></u>, <u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 26<br/><b><u><a aonid=\"563\" game-obj=\"Rules\">Unspecific Lore</a></u></b>: DC 24<br/><b><u><a aonid=\"563\" game-obj=\"Rules\">Specific Lore</a></u></b>: DC 21"
        },
        {
            "name": "Kobold Adoration",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary pg. 63",
                        "alt": "Bestiary pg. 63",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                    },
                    "page": 63
                }
            ],
            "subtype": "sidebar",
            "sidebar_type": "related_creatures",
            "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
            "image": {
                "type": "image",
                "name": "Related Creatures",
                "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
            },
            "html": "Some kobold groups are fond of chimera guardians or pets, but few kobolds have the bravery or resources to keep a chimera happy for long. While chimeras are often pressed into service by more intelligent creatures, it\u2019s also not unheard of for a chimera to keep a herd of unintelligent animals\u2014lions, goats, or even serpents\u2014as both companions and food supply."
        }
    ],
